                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12952402" author="njiang" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2009 02:58:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed a fix for this issue by introduce a new option of bridgeEndpoint,  if this option is true,  HttpProducer will ignore the message header of Exchange.HTTP_URI .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=813653&amp;amp;view=rev&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=813653&amp;amp;view=rev&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TODO update the wiki page for it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12952502" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2009 05:32:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Willem I think there is more to it, when in bridge it should also do a &lt;tt&gt;throwExceptionOnFailure=false&lt;/tt&gt; to be able to send the reply 100% back as is. (even if there was a http error 500 or the likes)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12952534" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 11 Sep 2009 05:36:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Willem I think just stating on the http wiki page that when you use &lt;tt&gt;bridgeEndpoint=true&lt;/tt&gt; then you should often also set &lt;tt&gt;throwExceptionOnFailure=false&lt;/tt&gt;. Eg if we just clearly document this then the end user have the freedom to decide whether to use both options or not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12952163" author="njiang" created="Sun, 13 Sep 2009 10:00:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated wiki page for it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12954904" author="thomasle" created="Fri, 12 Feb 2010 10:10:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the fix, I came across the same problem.&lt;br/&gt;
unfortunately it seems that the CamelHttpPath is still set to the old value of the jetty component. The path gets then added to the endpoint uri of the http component. So a &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;setHeader headerName=&quot;CamelHttpPath&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;constant&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/constant&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/setHeader&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
is still needed. Is this expected behaviour or could that be fixed inside the bridgeEndpoint option as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12954883" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 12 Feb 2010 10:13:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thomas create a new ticket and attach a unit test / sample that demonstrates the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12956430" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 3 Jun 2010 07:23:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing old resolved issues&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
